# Plan de Implementación — CRM Backend (v4.0)

La UI está 100% lista. Este plan convierte el CRM de una demo estática a un producto real conectado a Supabase, módulo por módulo.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> El orden de las fases es crítico. Cada fase tiene dependencias de la anterior. No saltar pasos.

---

## Estado Actual

- ✅ UI completa (todos los módulos del CRM)
- ✅ `@supabase/supabase-js` instalado
- ✅ Organización Supabase disponible (`Daniel Org` — `vfolazstlqsaikrcswkr`)
- ⚠️ Se usará un **proyecto Supabase nuevo y dedicado** — completamente separado del proyecto AcrosHub (plataforma educativa)
- ❌ Proyecto Supabase para el CRM **aún no creado**
- ❌ Tablas CRM no existen aún
- ❌ El CRM usa datos mockeados hardcodeados en cada componente

> [!IMPORTANT]
> El proyecto AcrosHub (`vbzpvjikkvwlcadughmm`) es de uso exclusivo para la plataforma educativa. El CRM tendrá su **propio proyecto Supabase independiente** para separar ambientes, datos y costos.

---

## Fase 0 — Crear Nuevo Proyecto Supabase
**Estimado: 15 min**

Antes de cualquier migración, se debe crear el proyecto Supabase dedicado al CRM.

### 0.1 Crear el proyecto
- **Organización:** Daniel Org (`vfolazstlqsaikrcswkr`)
- **Nombre sugerido:** `acrosoft-crm`
- **Región:** `us-east-1` (misma que AcrosHub para consistencia)
- **Costo:** $0/mes (plan Free)

### 0.2 Obtener credenciales
Una vez creado, copiar de la Dashboard de Supabase:
```
Settings → API → Project URL
Settings → API → anon public key
```

### 0.3 Crear archivo `.env`
```env
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://<nuevo-project-id>.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<nueva-anon-key>
```

### 0.4 Inicializar cliente Supabase en el frontend
Crear/actualizar `src/lib/supabase.ts`:
```ts
import { createClient } from '@supabase/supabase-js'

export const supabase = createClient(
  import.meta.env.VITE_SUPABASE_URL,
  import.meta.env.VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
)
```

> [!TIP]
> El proyecto nuevo del CRM incluirá automáticamente el schema de `auth.users` de Supabase, que es lo único que necesitamos como base para las tablas CRM.

---

## Fase 1 — Base de Datos (Supabase Migrations)
**Estimado: 1 día**

Crear todas las tablas del CRM en Supabase con RLS activado. Orden de creación por dependencias:

### 1.1 `crm_contacts`
```sql
CREATE TABLE crm_contacts (
  id            uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  created_at    timestamptz DEFAULT now(),
  user_id       uuid REFERENCES auth.users NOT NULL,
  name          text NOT NULL,
  email         text,
  phone         text,
  company       text,
  stage         text DEFAULT 'lead',
  tags          text[] DEFAULT '{}',
  notes         text,
  custom_fields jsonb DEFAULT '{}'
);
ALTER TABLE crm_contacts ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "Users manage own contacts" ON crm_contacts
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id) WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

### 1.2 `crm_appointments`
```sql
CREATE TABLE crm_appointments (
  id           uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  created_at   timestamptz DEFAULT now(),
  user_id      uuid REFERENCES auth.users NOT NULL,
  contact_id   uuid REFERENCES crm_contacts ON DELETE SET NULL,
  date         date NOT NULL,
  hour         int NOT NULL,
  duration_min int DEFAULT 30,
  service      text,
  status       text DEFAULT 'confirmed' CHECK (status IN ('confirmed','cancelled')),
  notes        text
);
ALTER TABLE crm_appointments ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "Users manage own appointments" ON crm_appointments
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id) WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

### 1.3 `crm_blocked_slots`
```sql
CREATE TABLE crm_blocked_slots (
  id          uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  created_at  timestamptz DEFAULT now(),
  user_id     uuid REFERENCES auth.users NOT NULL,
  type        text NOT NULL CHECK (type IN ('hours','fullday','range')),
  date        date,
  start_hour  int,
  end_hour    int,
  range_start date,
  range_end   date,
  reason      text
);
ALTER TABLE crm_blocked_slots ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "Users manage own blocks" ON crm_blocked_slots
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id) WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

### 1.4 `crm_pipeline_deals`
```sql
CREATE TABLE crm_pipeline_deals (
  id           uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  created_at   timestamptz DEFAULT now(),
  user_id      uuid REFERENCES auth.users NOT NULL,
  contact_id   uuid REFERENCES crm_contacts ON DELETE SET NULL,
  title        text NOT NULL,
  stage        text NOT NULL,
  value        numeric DEFAULT 0,
  currency     text DEFAULT 'USD',
  notes        text,
  custom_fields jsonb DEFAULT '{}'
);
ALTER TABLE crm_pipeline_deals ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "Users manage own deals" ON crm_pipeline_deals
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id) WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

### 1.5 `crm_forms` + `crm_form_submissions`
```sql
CREATE TABLE crm_forms (
  id              uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  created_at      timestamptz DEFAULT now(),
  user_id         uuid REFERENCES auth.users NOT NULL,
  name            text NOT NULL,
  fields          jsonb NOT NULL DEFAULT '[]',
  submit_label    text DEFAULT 'Enviar',
  success_action  text DEFAULT 'popup' CHECK (success_action IN ('popup','redirect')),
  success_message text,
  success_image   text DEFAULT 'icon' CHECK (success_image IN ('icon','logo')),
  redirect_url    text,
  slug            text UNIQUE
);
ALTER TABLE crm_forms ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "Users manage own forms" ON crm_forms
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id) WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);

CREATE TABLE crm_form_submissions (
  id         uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  created_at timestamptz DEFAULT now(),
  form_id    uuid REFERENCES crm_forms NOT NULL,
  data       jsonb NOT NULL DEFAULT '{}'
);
ALTER TABLE crm_form_submissions ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
-- Submissions son escribibles por cualquiera (formulario público) pero legibles solo por el dueño del form
CREATE POLICY "Anyone can submit" ON crm_form_submissions FOR INSERT WITH CHECK (true);
CREATE POLICY "Form owner reads submissions" ON crm_form_submissions FOR SELECT
  USING (EXISTS (SELECT 1 FROM crm_forms WHERE crm_forms.id = form_id AND crm_forms.user_id = auth.uid()));
```

### 1.6 `crm_calendar_config`
```sql
CREATE TABLE crm_calendar_config (
  id             uuid PRIMARY KEY DEFAULT gen_random_uuid(),
  user_id        uuid REFERENCES auth.users UNIQUE NOT NULL,
  name           text,
  description    text,
  duration_min   int DEFAULT 30,
  buffer_min     int DEFAULT 10,
  slug           text UNIQUE,
  linked_form_id uuid REFERENCES crm_forms ON DELETE SET NULL,
  availability   jsonb DEFAULT '{"mon":{"start":9,"end":18},"tue":{"start":9,"end":18},"wed":{"start":9,"end":18},"thu":{"start":9,"end":18},"fri":{"start":9,"end":18}}',
  google_token   jsonb
);
ALTER TABLE crm_calendar_config ENABLE ROW LEVEL SECURITY;
CREATE POLICY "Users manage own calendar config" ON crm_calendar_config
  USING (auth.uid() = user_id) WITH CHECK (auth.uid() = user_id);
```

